You wouldn't use a named Ruby method for something like this. You'd typically use a Proc or block.<p><pre><code>    [1,2,3].map{ |x| x * 2 }
</code></pre>
or if you wanted to reuse the block for other things<p><pre><code>    transform = lambda { |x| x * 2 }
    [1,2,3].map(&transform)</code></pre>
